      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Topliner MAGNIFICENT STORM NZ (3) made it three from three this time in when leading from wider to win the Mount Eden Sprint by 7.5m last start. Came from the back row to land the Pinjarra Cup prior. Won this race from the second line last year. The low draw should see him do it again. HUGOTASTIC NZ (1) showed improvement last start when beaten 1.6m into third at Gloucester Park. The inside draw can see him competitive. MIGHTY RONALDO (10) has improved with racing this time in and could be ready to peak after his last-start second to star pacer Minstrel. Tricky draw for Golden Nugget winner WAVERIDER (9) but he did well to place from a wide barrier behind Magnificent Storm when resuming in the Mount Eden Sprint and has won three of five second-up attempts.",
